{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01M1KNTygMwLAaRRN7niFTWp","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Duplo\n2\t\n3\tCreate or clone from whatever you've got — screenshots, a demo video,\n4\tdoc pages, a website, a one-line description — no source code required.\n5\tDrives Claude Code or Codex through phased builds via mcloop, turning\n6\treferences into working software.\n7\t\n8\tThe user creates a project directory and drops in whatever reference\n9\tmaterial they have. Running `duplo` from that directory analyzes the\n10\tmaterials, identifies the product to build or clone, extracts features\n11\tand visual design details, generates a build plan, and uses mcloop to\n12\tbuild it. Running `duplo` again detects new files the user has added,\n13\tre-scrapes any product docs, and appends new tasks for anything that\n14\twas missed. The cycle is: add reference material, run duplo, let\n15\tmcloop build, test, add more reference material if needed, run duplo\n16\tagain.\n17\t\n18\tPython 3.11+, depends on McLoop. Uses Claude Code via McLoop for all\n19\tcode generation. Ruff for linting, pytest for tests. Keep modules\n20\tshort and focused. This is a thin orchestration layer, not a framework.\n21\t\n22\t**ARCHITECTURE NOTE**: The old subcommand model (duplo init, duplo\n23\trun, duplo next) has been replaced. The new model is a single `duplo`\n24\tcommand with no required arguments. It runs from the current directory\n25\tand auto-detects whether this is a first run or an update based on\n26\twhether `.duplo/` exists. The redesign in progress (Phases 3-7)\n27\trestructures the input contract so user intent lives in a typed,\n28\treviewable `SPEC.md` rather than in interactive prompts and ambient\n29\tdirectory scanning.\n30\t\n31\t# Phase 1: Bootstrapping (complete)\n32\t\n33\t- [x] Project scaffolding\n34\t  - [x] Create duplo package with __init__.py and main.py entry point\n35\t  - [x] Add CLI argument parser: duplo <url>, duplo run, duplo next"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1d5a0bb2-dafd-476c-8755-3edf150f4691","uuid":"89246fcf-6dd2-4b55-a4a2-5ced8929499d","timestamp":"2026-05-16T13:38:28.703Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/mhcoen/proj/duplo/PLAN.md","content":"# Duplo\n\nCreate or clone from whatever you've got — screenshots, a demo video,\ndoc pages, a website, a one-line description — no source code required.\nDrives Claude Code or Codex through phased builds via mcloop, turning\nreferences into working software.\n\nThe user creates a project directory and drops in whatever reference\nmaterial they have. Running `duplo` from that directory analyzes the\nmaterials, identifies the product to build or clone, extracts features\nand visual design details, generates a build plan, and uses mcloop to\nbuild it. Running `duplo` again detects new files the user has added,\nre-scrapes any product docs, and appends new tasks for anything that\nwas missed. The cycle is: add reference material, run duplo, let\nmcloop build, test, add more reference material if needed, run duplo\nagain.\n\nPython 3.11+, depends on McLoop. Uses Claude Code via McLoop for all\ncode generation. Ruff for linting, pytest for tests. Keep modules\nshort and focused. This is a thin orchestration layer, not a framework.\n\n**ARCHITECTURE NOTE**: The old subcommand model (duplo init, duplo\nrun, duplo next) has been replaced. The new model is a single `duplo`\ncommand with no required arguments. It runs from the current directory\nand auto-detects whether this is a first run or an update based on\nwhether `.duplo/` exists. The redesign in progress (Phases 3-7)\nrestructures the input contract so user intent lives in a typed,\nreviewable `SPEC.md` rather than in interactive prompts and ambient\ndirectory scanning.\n\n# Phase 1: Bootstrapping (complete)\n\n- [x] Project scaffolding\n  - [x] Create duplo package with __init__.py and main.py entry point\n  - [x] Add CLI argument parser: duplo <url>, duplo run, duplo next","numLines":35,"startLine":1,"totalLines":1120}}}
