{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CWbgUck7rsSSoZUt4ccENk","type":"tool_result","content":"69:- [x] After all checklist tasks are complete, automatically run a bug audit/fix cycle\n70:   - [x] Add a function that runs a Claude Code session to audit the codebase and write BUGS.md listing only actual defects (crashes, incorrect behavior, unhandled errors, security issues), not style or refactoring\n71:   - [x] If BUGS.md contains bugs, run a second session scoped to fixing only the bugs listed in BUGS.md, then delete BUGS.md\n73:   - [x] Add a --no-audit flag to skip the bug audit cycle\n94:- [x] BUGS.md resume: skip audit if BUGS.md already exists\n101:- [x] Debugging instruction in task prompt (read crash reports first)\n105:- [x] Post-fix verification: after each bug fix succeeds and checks pass, run a focused review session on only the changed files to verify the fix did not introduce new bugs. Feed it the original bug description and the diff. If it finds a problem, feed it back into the fix loop before committing.\n106:- [x] Pre-fix bug verification: after the audit writes BUGS.md, run a separate verification session that reads each reported bug and checks it against the actual source code. Remove any bug that is incorrect (code doesn't match the description, the issue was already handled, the bug is hypothetical). Print to the terminal: \"Verifying N bugs...\" then for each bug either \"CONFIRMED: <file:line> <title>\" or \"REMOVED: <file:line> <title> (reason)\". Rewrite BUGS.md with only confirmed bugs before the fix cycle runs. If all bugs are removed, skip the fix cycle and print \"All reported bugs were false positives.\"\n107:- [x] Two-round audit cycle: run the full audit/verify/fix cycle twice. The second round catches bugs introduced by the first round's fixes. After the second round completes, save the audit hash and stop. Do not loop beyond two rounds.\n108:- [x] Non-destructive BUGS.md: mcloop audit must append new findings to an existing BUGS.md, not overwrite it. Include the audit prompt instruction to read the existing BUGS.md first and only report bugs not already listed.\n113:  - \">>> [AUDIT] Scanning for bugs...\" then dots, then a numbered list of found bugs with file, severity, and title\n114:  - \">>> [VERIFY] Verifying N bugs...\" then for each bug print CONFIRMED or REMOVED with a one-line reason\n115:  - \">>> [FIX] Fixing N bugs...\" then for each bug as it's fixed, print the bug title and a brief explanation of the fix\n122:- [x] Standalone `audit` subcommand: run a bug audit without running the task loop\n127:Adds an interactive debugging mode for hard runtime bugs that survive\n135:The debugging playbook this enforces:\n165:   - [x] Create `mcloop/investigator.py` with a function that takes bug context (crash report, user description, failure history, source code summary) and produces an investigation PLAN.md following the debugging playbook\n166:   - [x] The prompt for plan generation must include: the debugging playbook (reproduce, instrument, isolate, inspect, fix, clean up), instruction to create standalone probes for unclear subsystems, instruction to search the web for working examples before writing code, the \"What has been tried\" section populated from any available failure history\n168:   - [x] Add tests with sample bug descriptions verifying the generated plan contains research steps, isolation steps, and verification steps\n172:   - [x] Branch naming convention: `investigate-<slug>` where slug is derived from the bug description\n179:   - [x] Gather bug context from multiple sources (DiagnosticReports, .mcloop/last-run.log, piped stdin, --log file, description argument)\n193:   - [x] Use the app interaction layer to repeat the actions that triggered the original bug\n199:   - [x] Share bug context gathering code between investigate and any future fixbug command (same sources: DiagnosticReports, logs, piped input, description)\n202:   - [x] E